  "prompt": "How do I set up a Yahoo! account in China?",
  "response": "Setting up a Yahoo! account in China is similar to setting up an account in other countries, but there are a few considerations due to China's internet regulations. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n### Step-by-Step Guide to Setting Up a Yahoo! Account in China:\n\n1. **Access Yahoo! Website**:\n   - Open your web browser and go to the Yahoo! website. The URL is [https://www.yahoo.com](https://www.yahoo.com).\n   - Note: Due to internet restrictions in China, you might need to use a VPN to access Yahoo! if it is blocked by the Great Firewall.\n\n2. **Sign Up**:\n   - On the Yahoo! homepage, click on the **\"Sign In\"** or **\"Sign Up\"** button, usually located at the top-right corner.\n   - Select **\"Create an Account\"** or **\"Sign Up\"** to begin the registration process.\n\n3. **Fill in Your Information**:\n   - **First Name**: Enter your first name.\n   - **Last Name**: Enter your last name.\n   - **Email Address**: Choose a unique email address (e.g., yourname@yahoo.com).\n   - **Password**: Create a strong password. Make sure it includes a mix of letters, numbers, and special characters.\n   - **Mobile Number**: Enter your mobile phone number. Yahoo! will use this for verification and account recovery.\n   - **Birthdate**: Enter your birth date.\n\n4. **Verification**:\n   - Yahoo! will send a verification code to your mobile phone or email. Enter the code to verify your account.\n   - If you\u2019re using a Chinese phone number, ensure that you can receive international messages or use an email address for verification.\n\n5. **Agree to Terms**:\n   - Read Yahoo!'s **Terms of Service** and **Privacy Policy**, then agree to them by checking the box.\n\n6. **Complete Registration**:\n   - Click **\"Continue\"** or **\"Sign Up\"** to complete the registration process.\n\n7. **Set Up Your Account**:\n   - Once registered, you can set up your account by adding a profile picture, configuring security settings, and customizing your preferences.\n\n### Important Notes:\n\n- **VPN Usage**: Yahoo! services might be blocked in China, so you may need to use a reliable VPN to access Yahoo! during the setup process and for future use.\n- **Email Accessibility**: Ensure that you can regularly access your Yahoo! email. You may want to link it to a mobile app or another email service for easier access.\n- **Security**: Enable two-factor authentication (2FA) for added security, especially when using your account in regions with internet restrictions.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to set up a Yahoo! account in China, provided you have a stable internet connection and, if necessary, a VPN.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
